description.narrative: By 2023, parents, teachers, religious leaders, communities and adolescents have enhanced knowledge, skills and attitudes to protect girls and boys from violence and exploitation through the scale of Positive Discipline, Positive Parenting and Cambodia PROTECT child protection programmes., which contributes to Access To Justice, Adolescent Empowerment, Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Early Childhood Development, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Learning Outcomes, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, girls and boys including adolescents, living with families and outside of family care are increasingly free from violence and exploitation and from the threat of violence and exploitation in their homes, schools and communities and in institutions, including during humanitarian situations.

description.narrative: The Action Plan to Prevent and Respond to Violence against Children 2017-2019 is being implemented nationwide with key activities focusing its implementation in 16 provinces, benefitting at least 123,000 girls and boys. As part of the Action Plan, the national five-year behavior change communication campaign towards ending violence against children and unnecessary family separation (Cambodia PROTECT) was launched by the Ministry of Social Affairs, Veterans and Youth Rehabilitation (MoSVY) with support from UNICEF in February 2020. Communication materials have been disseminated through mass media and social media, reaching at least 2.7 million people across the country. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/08/2020
